Title: Disable desktop-only KIconThemes tools and plugin on iOS

## Problem

The KIconThemes build includes several desktop-only targets:

- `kiconfinder`, an executable utility.
- `ksvg2icns`, a macOS utility that launches Apple's `iconutil`.
- `KIconEnginePlugin`, a dynamically loaded Qt image plugin.

iOS applications cannot launch arbitrary external processes, so utilities such
as `iconutil` cannot be invoked. Standalone helper executables are not useful
inside an iOS application bundle. In addition, iOS applications require their
code to be linked into the application and do not support loading arbitrary
plugin modules in the same manner as desktop Qt installations.

These targets either fail to build for iOS or produce artifacts that cannot be
used on the platform.

## Proposed change

Do not build or install `kiconfinder`, `ksvg2icns`, or `KIconEnginePlugin` when
targeting iOS. The main KIconThemes library and its Qt Quick support remain
available.

The `QProcess` invocation in `ksvg2icns` is also guarded for iOS as a defensive
measure for configurations that compile that source independently.

## Impact

iOS builds retain the KIconThemes library API but omit desktop command-line
tools and the dynamically loaded icon engine plugin. Other Apple platforms and
all non-iOS platforms retain their current behavior.

